according  to  the  order  in  which  they  arrived  at  the  Committee. 
This  is  not  going  to  be,  like  most  everything  in  the  Senate,  based 
on  seniority.  I  think  having  people  speak  other  than  on  the  basis 
in which they arrived. If they arrived early, they should speak ear-
lier. 

And I just happen to believe in that. But today we’ll also use the 
seniority  system  for  that.  We’ll  start  with  Senator  Cantwell,  then 
we’ll go to Senator Snowe and then back and forth. 

