ations  in  the  future  is  the  Alaska  Natural  Gas  Pipeline  which  will 
be thousands of jobs, a lot of investment, but will benefit this coun-
try greatly. 

With that project there’s about $2 billion worth of road projects— 
infrastructure  that’s  necessary  to  construct  that  project  and  get 
material  to  the  sites.  Is  that  something  that  you’d  be  willing  to 
work  with  the  Alaska  delegation  to  figure  out  how  to  solve  that 
